Package: storm
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: A platform for extensible languages
 Storm is a language system for extensible languages. It allows
 creating multiple languages and DSLs that are able to operate
 in close cooperation. Not too dissimilar from LISP systems, but
 with custom syntax.
Recommends: storm-crypto, storm-graphics, storm-layout, storm-ui, storm-presentation, storm-sql

Package: storm-crypto
Architecture: amd64
Depends: storm (= ${source:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Cryptographic library for Storm
 Cryptographic primitives (for example for estabilshing SSL tunnels)
 for Storm.

Package: storm-graphics
Architecture: amd64
Depends: storm (= ${source:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Graphics library for Storm
 Provides the ability to load various image types to Storm programs.

Package: storm-layout
Architecture: amd64
Depends: storm (= ${source:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Layout library for Storm
 This library provides a language extension for declaring layouts
 in Storm.

Package: storm-ui
Architecture: amd64
Depends: storm (= ${source:Version}), storm-layout, libgtk-3, pango, cairo, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: UI library for Storm (using Gtk3)
 UI library for Storm using Gtk+.

Package: storm-presentation
Architecture: amd64
Depends: storm (= ${source:Version}), storm-gui, storm-layout, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Presentation library for Storm
 Library with language extensions for conveniently creating and showing
 presentations in Storm.

Package: storm-sql
Architecture: amd64
Depends: storm (= ${source:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: SQL library for Storm
 Generic SQL database interface to Storm (complete with custom syntax).
 Provides bindings for SQLite at the moment.

Package: progvis
Section: education
Architecture: amd64
Depends: storm (= ${source:Version}), storm-ui, storm-sql, storm-layout, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Program visualization tool for C/C++ (and others)
 A program visualization tool (written in Storm). Supports a subset
 of C/C++, and other languages supported by Storm. Aimed at showing
 how concurrent programs interact with pointers/references and other
 fundamental programming concepts.

